s nearly three times the size of its previous fund the  billion green equity investors iv lp leonard green had previously raised  billion for its third fund in   million for its second fund in  and  million for its debut fund in  at the end of  leonard green was ranked  among the  largest private equity firms globally founded in  leonard green  partners has invested in  companies with aggregate value of  billion among the firms historical investments are the following rite aid  big  sporting goods  petco   leonard green and tpg capital invested  million to acquire the pet supplies retailer as part of a  million buyout within two years they sold most of it in a public offering that valued the company at  billion petco’s market value more than doubled by the end of  and the firms would ultimately realize a gain of  billion then in  the private equity firms took petco private again for  billion leslies poolmart june  sports authority february  varsity brands april  ftd group inc october  leonard green announced a  million going private acquisition of ftd in which the firm invested  million on february   ftd completed an initial public offering davids bridal november  priscilla of boston april  the container store july  whole foods market november   aersale january  lucky brand jeans in december  for  million from kate spade  company motorpsorts aftermarket group joann stores  for b  bj wholesale  historyedit history of private equity and venture capital early history origins of modern private equity the s leveraged buyout boom the s leveraged buyout and the venture capital bubble the s dotcom bubble to the credit crunch v t e leonard green was founded by leonard i green in  after separating from gibbons green and van amerongen ltd gibbons green a merchant bank which he had cofounded in  with edward i gibbons and lewis w van amerongen the firms eponymous founder leonard i green died in  leaving the firm to be run by john g danhakl peter j nolan and jonathan d sokoloff w