or b  bj wholesale  historyedit history of private equity and venture capital early history origins of modern private equity the s leveraged buyout boom the s leveraged buyout and the venture capital bubble the s dotcom bubble to the credit crunch v t e leonard green was founded by leonard i green in  after separating from gibbons green and van amerongen ltd gibbons green a merchant bank which he had cofounded in  with edward i gibbons and lewis w van amerongen the firms eponymous founder leonard i green died in  leaving the firm to be run by john g danhakl peter j nolan and jonathan d sokoloff who had been greens bankers at drexel burnham lambert and donaldson lufkin  jenrette prior to joining the firm the firms predecessor gibbons green had completed over  transactions with an aggregate purchase price of over  billion from  through its dissolution in  and was among the earliest practitioners of the leveraged buyout and management buyout among its most notable transactions were the purchase of budget rent a car  from transamerica in  as well as the acquisition of kash n karry food stores the firm completed the  buyout of purex industries but had to withdraw from the  buyout of insurer argonaut due to the stock market crash in that year the dissolution of gibbons green and the formation of leonard green  partners is primarily attributed to the failure of two buyouts ohio mattress company and shellerglobe corporation ohio mattress company – on march   ohio mattress company known for its sealy and stearns  foster brands was sold to gibbons green for  billion a price that many observers at the time believed too high in august  the junk bond market collapsed leaving first boston unable to redeem hundreds of millions it had lent for the leveraged buyout of ohio mattress the amount lent  million was  percent of first boston’s equity capital and the bank was forced to seek a bailout from credit suisse leading subsequently to the takeover of first boston and the formation of cs first boston the incident became known as the burning bed and ultimately gibbons green was forced to offer a significant equity stake in the company in order to secure financing shellerglobe corporation – gibbons green bought shellerglobe jointly with united technologies from knoll international when the company faced an immediate cash squeeze united technologies stepped in to buy out the shares owned by gibbons green with no other options gibbons green realized a  million loss on its investment gibbons green accused knoll of providing misleading or incomplete information however observers believed the firm had not conducted proper due diligence referencesedit  contact leonard green and partners leonardgreencom retrieved    dog on the loose wall street west vca antech inc went los angeles business journal january   retrieved on august   so in september of  vca was taken private by a group that included the west los angeles lbo shop leonard green  partners  a b source preqin  tracy tennille  leonard green keeping up with the jones  deal journal  wsj blogswsjcom retrieved    rite aid sets an extension on payment of  billion in debt new york times  retrieved    company news managementled group to buy petco for  million new york times  retrieved     equity firms to acquire petco the new york times    leslies poolmart taken private in  million deal  new york times nytimescom  retrieved    steinhauer jennifer  gart offers  million for  of sports authority new york times retrieved    company news sports authority and gart sports agree to merge new york times  retrieved    company news uniform maker agrees to  million buyout new york times  retrieved    company news  green equity investors to buy ftd for  million the new york times  retrieved    today in business  federated sells bridal unit  nytimescom new york times  retrieved    wilson eric  lifting the veil on seventh the new york times   hughes elaine  private firm buys container store usatodaycom retrieved    who